    <item>
      <title>Search Git Users</title>
      <link>https://mihaigmarin.github.io/post/search-git-users/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 21:42:46 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://mihaigmarin.github.io/post/search-git-users/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s say we want to change our git username to another one. Instead of checking manually if the username is already taken, we can automate this process by writing a script named &lt;code&gt;fgitusr&lt;/code&gt;. The content of the script looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;code&#34;&gt;Code&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# Check regex rules&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; !&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;~ ^&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;0-9a-zA-Z&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]{&lt;/span&gt;1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;}[&lt;/span&gt;0-9a-zA-Z&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;\-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;*&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;0-9a-zA-Z&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]{&lt;/span&gt;1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;$&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    echo &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt; DOESN&amp;#39;T MATCH REGEX&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    exit &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# Check if usersname exists&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl --output /dev/null --silent  --head --fail &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;https://github.com/&lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt; $? -eq &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    echo &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;USER &lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt; EXISTS&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    echo &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;USER &lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt; DOESN&amp;#39;T EXIST&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The main idea is that we use &lt;code&gt;curl&lt;/code&gt; to look if the url &lt;code&gt;https://github.com/&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; is a valid link. If it is, then the user exist.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Read Html inside terminal</title>
      <link>https://mihaigmarin.github.io/post/read-html-inside-terminal/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2024 11:00:36 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>https://mihaigmarin.github.io/post/read-html-inside-terminal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This can be done by using &lt;code&gt;curl&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;pandoc&lt;/code&gt;.
The command looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl &amp;lt;url&amp;gt; | pandoc -f html -t plain | less
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After that you can go up and down with &lt;code&gt;j&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;k&lt;/code&gt; keys.
With this command you can read directly in the terminal.
If you want to store the information in a text file,
you could use this command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl &amp;lt;url&amp;gt; | pandoc -f html -t plain &amp;gt; file.txt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Where &lt;code&gt;file.txt&lt;/code&gt; is the name of the file where the information
is stored.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
